message:
Refactor and use twistd to run the server

I wanted to add a bit more structure before proceeding to add new
twisted resources.

slybot integration and adding extraction to fetch api

This also improves the scrapy initialization and configuration.

Add project to the api request path

This will unify the way projects are specified at the API level and will
make it possible to do check project access in a unified way.

Add spec API

This api can be used to fetch the specifications of slybot spiders.

Saving of specs

This implements saving of slybot specs. It also improves general error
handling.

Generate a list of spider names when spec/spiders is called

Closes #2

change how links are returned and document

Refs #4

Add move and delete for spiders

Closes #6
Prepare as2 to merge into portia
README: fix path to requirements.txt, re-order sections giving prominence to installation & usage

installing from requirements.txt requires sudo on Mac

Also, since we ```cd slyd``` already, we don't need slyd/requirements.txt
Added instructions to run portia with vagrant.
update README doc for deployment with scrapyd

DOC: typos+scrapyd  docs

corrected some typos and re-added latest scrapyd doc from https://github.com/scrapinghub/portia/commit/c2463bdd1a6bc2f190d485984963a452223ab317
#128 Update docs to warn users not to run scrapyd in their project directory
Update README to describe new features. Update provision.sh script

added dependency, moved instruction

Made it explicit that dependencies are for ubuntu and debian
Port App to Ember-Cli. Start Plugin System. Adds #133 and #136

Noting that this is more or less a WYSIWYG web scraper. I know that I would have found this great tool a little sooner if that search keyword was included (a little SEO tweak I guess). Closes #111
